      "content": "I frame it as \"outdated\" because the scientific consensus overwhelmingly demonstrates that coal is a major contributor to climate change and air pollution. While I acknowledge that local economies depend on it, the long-term global and environmental costs of coal are far greater than the short-term economic benefits in any single region. The goal of modern policy must be to align economic activity with planetary health, making the shift away from coal a necessity, not just a preference.",
